I can see her with Kenny, they are both laid back and Kenny seems to be a good guy. Interestingly enough, Barnette was also someone that Lauren spoke with frequently, can you see that being a match? Lauren and Cameron both insinuated that they chose each other early on, so I don't think any of the other guys had a chance. I am curious as to why they still had to date others after they confessed their love to one another. Netflix hoping for drama?

snippet.textDisplay:
Jessica (to Mark's face): Barnett is so sexy...
Mark (at Reunion): I wish you had told me from the beginning...


I think the title "Love is Blind" not only refers to falling in love without seeing someone, but the act of Loving someone can make you blind to your madness. The rose colored glasses (Mark jumping mental hoops trying to justify an incompatible relationship) and inability to move past toxic cycles. Each couple represented different outcomes of love. Healthy love, Toxic love, Unreciprocated Love, Platonic Love, How love plays out when you're not at peace with yourself (Carlton) ... and the ability of those kinds of love to fit into traditional conventions of marriage and everyday life.
